description._content: Group portrait of members of Royal Australian Historical Society, taken on excursion to Linden. Standing on steps of Martin's Folly, an unfinished mansion begun By Sir James Martin c. 1878. This image is part of a collection entitled ‘Blue Mountains Excursions', which is available to view on the Royal Australian Historical Society's Historypin Channel. Access the collection at the following link: www.historypin.com/channels/view/id/48441/#|collections/v... Please feel free to comment on this or any of the other images in the collection. If you have more accurate information regarding the location and/or date of the image, we would love to hear from you!
